    • Constructor Detail

      • ChargingStation

        public ChargingStation(int id,
                       java.lang.String name,
                       java.lang.String[] kinds,
                       java.lang.String[] source,
                       float[][] energAm)
        Constructor of ChargingStation class.
        Parameters:
        id - The id of ChargingStation.
        name - The name of ChargingStation.
        kinds - It is a String array with the kinds of charging the ChargingStation supports. The arguments can to be "slow" for slow charging, or "fast" for fast charging. Accordingly the length of the array it creates so much Charger objects.
        source - It is a String array with the kinds of energy the ChargingStation supports. The arguments can to be "solar" for solar energy, "wind" for wind energy, "wave" for wave energy, "hydroelectric" for hydroelectric energy, "geothermal" for geothermal energy or "nonrenewable" foe nonrenewable energy sources. Accordingly the length of the array and the value of each cell, an object of the corresponding source of energy is created.
        energAm - An 2-dimention array. It contains the energies each kind of energy source is going to give to the ChargingStation at every update of the storage. The kinds of energy are refered in the same order that was given in the source array.

      • batteriesCharging

        public final java.util.ArrayList<ChargingEvent> batteriesCharging(java.lang.String kind)
        Checks the batteries which are for battery exchange to confirm which of them need charging. It returns an ArrayList structure with so ChargingEvent objects as the empty slots in the ChargingStation. The ChargingEvent objects do not need preProcessing function, only execution.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        An ArrayList structure with the ChargingEvent objects ready to be executed(only method execution() is needed).
